label: Dumb Woman's Lane
column5: To avoid murder; but keep their smuggling secret - villains cut out the tongue of the unfortunate woman who once lived on this lane.

label: Trollstigen (Norway)
column5: Dramatic mountain pass called 'Troll’s Path'; local legends of trolls abound.

label: Hanging Sword Alley
column5: Name said to come from a fencing school

label: Elfreth’s Alley
column5: Oldest continuously inhabited residential street in the US; site of many local ghost stories.

label: Fairy Bridge (Isle of Man)
column5: Manx superstition says greet the fairies when crossing or risk bad luck.

label: Bloody Lane
column5: Site of fierce Civil War fighting at Antietam; central to local ghost stories.

label: Witch Way
column5: Nods to Salem's infamous 17th-century witch trials and enduring witch lore.

label: Hell's Backbone Road
column5: A scenic but precarious route in Utah; name evokes danger and local frontier tales.

label: Sleepy Hollow Road
column5: Famously associated with Washington Irving’s 'The Legend of Sleepy Hollow.'

label: Moll Dyer Road
column5: Named for a 17th-century figure rumored to be a witch; local folklore persists.

label: Buca delle Fate
column5: 'Fairies' Bay'; local lore claims fairies once protected the coastline.

label: Teufelhofstrasse
column5: ‘Teufel’ = devil in German; associated with local devil legends and a themed hotel.
